# Nissan Consult Arduino Library

Fork of https://github.com/Crim/Arduino-Nissan-Consult-Library work.

This updates it with documentation gathered off the internet archive for reference due to the dead links. Prodimently the reference PDFs were saved and updated into this repo for reference.

## Overview

This project provides Arduino code to communicate with Nissan ECUs via the Consult protocol. You can purchase pre-built serial adapters on eBay or from China for around $15, or build your own using the schematics and documentation provided.

## Getting Started

### Hardware

You'll need a Nissan Consult serial adapter. 

1. **Buy Pre-built** - Available on eBay or from Chinese suppliers (~$15)
2. **Build Your Own** - See [DIY Consult Interface](#diy-consult-interface) below

### Installation

Include the library files in your Arduino project and import them in your sketch.

## Documentation

### DIY Consult Interface

If you prefer to build your own adapter, detailed information was orginally available here:  

[PLMS Developments - DIY Consult](documentation\plmsdevelopments.com-diy_consult.htm)

original website link : http://www.plmsdevelopments.com/diy_consult.htm

This resource includes:
- Complete schematic diagrams
- Protocol documentation
- Component lists

### Protocol & Reference Documentation

The following PDFs are available in the `documentation/` folder:

- **Protocol PDF** - Updated to Issue 6 (Consult protocol specification)
- **Generic Nissan ECU Data Register Table** - Common register definitions across Nissan models
- **Consult Interface Schematic Diagram** - Rev 4 (hardware design)
- **1999 A32 Maxima Register Details (OBDII)** - Model-specific register mapping

*Thanks to Randy for contributing the Maxima register details.*

## Extending This Library

This code is designed to be extended. The Consult protocol documentation in the `documentation/` folder provides enough detail to add additional functionality beyond the current implementation. If you improve or extend this code, please consider contributing back to the project!

## Credits

